<div id="timelinestext">
<p>Through the painstaking work of Dr.Maria Cotera, Linda Garcia Merchant, and the contributions of dozens of graduate and undergraduate students, we can begin situating Chicana Activism within a broader understanding of other kinds of civil rights activism. Each timeline reflects major events within an important faction of Civil Rights praxis - be that the more well-known Chicano rights movements, the second wave feminist movement, or a timeline of the Raza Unida Party's work. We add to these more well-known histories, our own timeline of Chicana Feminist activism.</p></div>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p> Click each button to turn on that timeline. Timelines can be collapsed using the hide button next to each timeline's title.<p>
